Sentencas: Ruthenium and gadolinia-doped ceria (Ru-CGO) composite nano-crystalline thin film anodes are demonstrated for the first time in self-supported micro-solid oxide fuel cells (mu SOFCs) for direct methane utilization, targeting development of microstructurally stable anodes under operation.
Titulo: Nanostructured ruthenium - gadolinia-doped ceria composite anodes for thin film solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Nano-composite thin film anodes are synthesized by co-sputtering from Ru metal and CGO oxide targets.
Titulo: Nanostructured ruthenium - gadolinia-doped ceria composite anodes for thin film solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Detailed electrical, crystalline and microstructural analyses were carried out on composite films to characterize properties as a function of Ru/CGO relative fraction.
Titulo: Nanostructured ruthenium - gadolinia-doped ceria composite anodes for thin film solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Microstructural stability of the composite film is compared to Ru metal film from conductivity and grain size behavior during 500 degrees C thermal treatments.
Titulo: Nanostructured ruthenium - gadolinia-doped ceria composite anodes for thin film solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Stress-relaxed composite thin film anodes were developed on self-supported mu SOFCs with yttria-stabilized zirconia thin film electrolytes and porous platinum cathodes.
Titulo: Nanostructured ruthenium - gadolinia-doped ceria composite anodes for thin film solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: mu SOFCs were tested with room temperature humidified methane as fuel and air as the oxidant, exhibited an open circuit voltage of 0.97 V and a peak power density of 275 mW cm(-2) at 485 degrees C. Microstructural stability of Ru-CGO composite anodes relative to metal electrodes is discussed.
Titulo: Nanostructured ruthenium - gadolinia-doped ceria composite anodes for thin film solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results suggest a general approach to synthesis of functional metal-oxide nano-composite thin films for electrodes in fuel cells and related energy conversion devices.
Titulo: Nanostructured ruthenium - gadolinia-doped ceria composite anodes for thin film solid oxide fuel cells
